{
  "doc_id": "31307",
  "text": "Many of the physiological functions of P-gp are still unknown [CITATION_1] . To better understand the functional roles of P-gp in the brain, it is essential to know its cellular localization under both physiological and pathological conditions. In the present study we directly compared the different protocols used for P-gp immunohistochemistry by [CITATION_2] and our group in normal rat brains and after kainate-induced seizures, using three different P-gp antibodies. Because freezing, pH, and dehydration are additional variables in immunohistochemical localization of proteins in rat brain [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , we examined such variables also with respect to P-gp immunostaining.",
